		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I would be careful taking what a teacher told you as the only authority. The reason is that there&#8217;s no way she can tell you everything. At best, you&#8217;re going to get adult guidance, which is fine, but is there anyone who hasn&#8217;t rebelled again adult guidance at least a little? Do you really want to end up using &#8220;四角張った&#8221; language all the time? That&#8217;s just as bad as being dramatic.</p>
